text: Churtan () is a rural locality (a village) in Uslinsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 474 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 37 km from Sterlitamak, 7 km from Verkhniye Usly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Churtan, Republic of Bashkortostan
